Anal tube short, slightly narrower distally, as long as last two chaetigers and with up to six transversal striations (
Figs 5B, C
; 
6E
). Posterior border provided with up to seven pairs of round, short papillae (but usually five pairs); marginal papillae with dorsal gradation in length, dorsal-most shorter, ventral-most papillae longer and slightly smaller than paired basal papillae (
Figs 5B, C
; 
6E
). Internal, unpaired ventral anal cirrus, long and crenulated (
Figs 5B, C
; 
6E
). Pair of glandular, digitate and wide basal papillae, usually larger and distinct from marginal papillae (
Fig. 5B, C
); some individuals presenting dark spots on basal cirri (
Fig. 5B
).
